.","German: occupational name for a cooper or the overseer of a wine cellar, from an agent derivative of Middle High German <i>kuofe</i> ‘vat, barrel’ (from Latin <i>cupa</i>).","German: possibly also from an agent derivative of Middle High German <i>kiffen</i> ‘to quarrel’, hence a nickname for a bickerer."]}]},{"name":"Jean","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]},{"name":"Jacques","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   James   and   Jacob .  In French there is no distinction between a form corresponding to <i>Jacob</i> and a form corresponding to <i>James</i>. This is a perennially popular French given name, and <i>Jacques</i> or <i>Jacques Bonhomme</i> has been used (like <i>John Bull</i> in English) as a typification of the ordinary citizen. In  Shakespeare's  time it was also used as an English name, pronounced ‘<b>jay</b>-kwez’, as in the case of the melancholy character Jacques in As You Like It. Though rarely, if ever, now used in Britain it is found in the United States."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Jean Jacques KIEFFER was born in 1480, in Zweibrücken, Zweibrücken, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany as the son of Michael KIEFFER. He married Maria Elisabetha SCHWEIKHARDT on 28 February 1530, in Zweibrücken, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died about 1540, in Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1480–Abt 1540":"1480–umbes 1540","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1485–1560":"1485–1560","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1505–1587":"1505–1587","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","28 February 1530":"28. veebruar 1530","1500":"1500","1587":"1587","Abt 1540":"umbes 1540","1485":"1485","1540":"1540","1450":"1450","1560":"1560","1480":"1480","1505":"1505","Zweibrücken, Zweibrücken, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Zweibrücken, Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa","Großheppach, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Großheppach, Weinstadt, Rems-Murr-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Française":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1480–Abt 1540":"1480–noin 1540","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1485–1560":"1485–1560","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1505–1587":"1505–1587","1450–Male":"1450–Kuollut","28 February 1530":"28. helmikuuta 1530","1500":"1500","1587":"1587","Abt 1540":"noin 1540","1485":"1485","1540":"1540","1450":"1450","1560":"1560","1480":"1480","1505":"1505","Zweibrücken, Zweibrücken, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Zweibrücken, Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa","Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Allemagne":"Zweibrücken, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa","Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Pfettisheim, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Ranska","Großheppach, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Großheppach, Weinstadt, Rems-Murr-Kreis, Baden-